						<summary>

						<p>Slab in front of the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription is dated in the cyclic year Nandana, Mārgasira, śu • • •, Uttarāyaṇa saṁkrānti.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land for offerings, repairs <hi rend="italic">etc.,</hi> of a temple and for feeding the ascetics and others. Mentions Pānuṁgalanāḍu.</p>						

						<p>The characters belong to about 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
